Usage: setWhatIfPortParameters [-help] <blackBoxCellName> [-cap <value>]
                               -cell <cell name> [-max_cap <value>]
                               [-max_fanout <integer>] [-max_trans <value>]
                               -pin <pin name> [-port <portName>]

-help                  # Prints out the command usage
<blackBoxCellName>     # name of the blackbox or blackblob cell
                       # (string, required)
-cap <value>           # Specifies the capacitance value in picoFarad
                       # (float, optional)
-cell <cell name>      # Specifies the name of library cell from which DRVs are
                       # inferred (string, required)
-max_cap <value>       # Specifies the maximum capacitance value
                       # (float, optional)
-max_fanout <integer>  # Specifies the maximum fanout value (int, optional)
-max_trans <value>     # Specifies the maximum transition value in nanoseconds
                       # (float, optional)
-pin <pin name>        # Specifies the name of pin from which DRVs are inferred
                       # (string, required)
-port <portName>       # Specifies the name of the clock port on which to set
                       # the value (string, optional)